            "old_string": "## P6: Kernel Subsystem Visualization (Educational Web UI)\n\nGoal: Add a sampled, educational observatory to kbox's web dashboard that\nvisualizes Linux kernel subsystem interactions through pixel-art animation.\nUse the house-cross-section narrative style from the Linux comic\n(hackmd.io/@sysprog/linux-comic), with cute penguin characters animated in the\nstyle of star-office-ui-v2 and tinyclaw's pixel-art office scenes.\n\nThis is kbox's differentiator vs containers/VMs: we intercept every syscall and\nroute it through LKL, so we can visualize kernel activity -- not static diagrams,\nbut sampled animations driven by real guest behavior. The SSE event stream is\nintentionally lossy (1% sampling for routine syscalls), so the visualization is\nan impressionistic view of subsystem activity, not a faithful per-syscall replay.\nAggregate counters from `/api/snapshot` (3s polling) provide the authoritative\nambient state for each room.",
