for pixel art\n- [ ] Implement penguin state machine: idle → walk → action → idle\n      (action = type/celebrate/error depending on syscall outcome)\n- [ ] Accessory compositing: draw base penguin frame, then overlay\n      accessory sprite at fixed offset\n- [ ] Elliptical shadow beneath each character (canvas arc + alpha)\n- [ ] Z-ordering by Y-position (draw back-to-front)\n- [ ] Speech bubble system: DOM overlay positioned above character,\n      auto-expire (3s), shows text from string table\n- [ ] Movement interpolation: smooth linear walk between room centers\n- [ ] Guest penguin pool: 6-8 reusable sprite instances, crowd badge\n      in Attic when overflow\n\nPhase 6b.5 -- Fixed-timestep animation queue:\n- [ ] Animation intent queue: SSE callbacks and snapshot deltas push\n      \"intents\" (move penguin X to room Y, show bubble Z, set room\n      glow level) into a FIFO queue\n- [ ] Fixed-timestep consumer: `requestAnimationFrame` loop consumes\n      intents at a capped rate (max N intents/frame), applies tweening\n      for position interpolation, and batches canvas redraws\n- [ ] Concurrent motion cap: max 4 simultaneous penguin walks; excess\n      intents queue until a slot frees\n- [ ] Subsystem-weighted intent selection: when the intent queue has\n      more entries than can be animated per frame, prefer intents that\n      target rooms not recently animated (round-robin across active\n      rooms). This prevents a flood of file_io events from starving\n      other rooms. Note: the server's 1% sampling is not controllable\n      client-side; this is purely a client-side prioritization of which\n      queued intents to visualize first. Rooms with no sampled events\n      still show activity via snapshot-driven ambient state.\n\nMilestone 1 exit criteria: kernel house renders with all rooms, penguins\nidle in their rooms, clicking \"demo\" button triggers canned walk/action\nsequences. No live data needed.\n\n#### Milestone 2: Telemetry Binding (Phas