            "content": "# kbox - Project Instructions\n\n## What is kbox\nRootless chroot via seccomp-unotify + LKL (Linux Kernel Library). Intercepts\nguest syscalls and routes them to an in-process Linux kernel. Linux-only, runs\non x86_64 and aarch64.\n\n## Build\nLinux-only. Never attempt to build on macOS.\n\n```bash\n# x86_64 (on node1)\nssh node1\ncd ~/TEMP/kbox && make BUILD=release\n\n# aarch64 (on lima VM)\nlima bash -c \"cd ~/TEMP/kbox && make BUILD=release LKL_DIR=lkl-aarch64\"\n\n# debug build (ASAN/UBSAN)\nmake\n```\n\nDeploy sources before building:\n- node1: `scp src/*.c node1:~/TEMP/kbox/src/` and headers similarly\n- lima: `lima bash -c \"cp -r /Users/jserv/playground/kbox/{src,include,tests,scripts,Makefile} ~/TEMP/kbox/\"`\n\n## Test\n```bash\nmake check-unit                              # 82 unit tests, no LKL needed\n./scripts/run-tests.sh ./kbox alpine.ext4    # 43 integration tests\nmake check-stress                            # stress tests (non-blocking)\n```\n\nTest image `alpine.ext4` lives in ~/TEMP/kbox/ on both node1 and lima.\n\n## Code Style\n- C11 (`-std=gnu11`), `-Wall -Wextra -Wpedantic -Wshadow`\n- Follow `.clang-format` for formatting\n- Filenames use hyphens, not underscores (e.g., `fd-table.c`, not `fd_table.c`)\n- Functions do one thing, max three indentation levels\n- No TODO comments, no stub implementations\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n### Source layout\n| Directory | Purpose |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `src/` | All C source files |\n| `include/kbox/` | Public headers |\n| `tests/unit/` | Unit tests (no LKL dependency) |\n| `tests/guest/` | Guest test programs (static, run inside kbox) |\n| `tests/stress/` | Stress test programs (static, run inside kbox) |\n| `scripts/` | Build helpers, test runners, git hooks |\n| `scripts/gdb/` | GDB helper commands |\n| `web/` | Frontend dashboard assets |\n| `docs/` | Documentation |\n\n### Key files\n- `src/seccomp-dispatch.c` -- main syscall dispatch (~3750 lines, largest file)\n- `src/seccomp-bpf.c` -- BPF filter generation\n- `src/fd-table.c` -- virtual FD table (two-range: low 0..1023, high 32768+)\n- `src/shadow-fd.c` -- memfd shadows for O_RDONLY files (enables mmap)\n- `src/path.c` -- path normalization and virtual/host routing\n- `src/elf.c` -- ELF parser, PT_INTERP extraction\n- `src/mount.c` -- mount profiles (raw, recommended, standard)\n- `include/kbox/lkl-wrap.h` -- LKL stat struct and ABI translation\n\n### Critical ABI rules\n- LKL uses asm-generic stat (128 bytes). Host x86_64 stat is 144 bytes.\n  Always use `struct kbox_lkl_stat` + `kbox_lkl_stat_to_host()`.\n- seccomp args[] zero-extend 32-bit values. Use `to_dirfd_arg()` for sign extension.\n- aarch64 O_* flags differ from asm-generic. Translate bidirectionally.\n\n### FD table design\n- `KBOX_FD_BASE=32768` splits virtual FDs into two ranges\n- `entries[]` for FDs >= 32768 (normal allocation)\n- `low_fds[1024]` for FDs 0..1023 (only via dup2/dup3)\n- Gap [1024, 32768) is untracked (documented limitation)\n\n### BPF filter\n- `close` is NOT in the allow list (goes through USER_NOTIF -> forward_close)\n- `sendmsg` IS in the allow list (child pre-exec SCM_RIGHTS)\n\n## Review Workflow\nImplement -> self-review -> Gemini + Codex MCP (parallel) -> consensus fixes -> rebuild + retest.\n",
